flowRoot.flowPara: May 03, the anniversary of the Declaration of Windhoek, is celebrated globally as the Press Freedom Day. It is an opportunity to celebrate the fundamental principles of press freedom; assess the state of press freedom throughout the world; defend the media from attacks on their independence; and pay tribute to journalists who have lost their lives in the line of duty.
